HEADWORD: Maltha
<hw>Mal"tha</hw> <pr>(m⟦acr⟧l"th⟦adot⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[L., fr. Gr. <grk>ma`lqa</grk>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A variety
of bitumen, viscid and tenacious, like pitch, unctuous to the touch, and
exhaling a bituminous odor.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Mortar.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Holland.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Malthus</ent>⟦br⟧
